	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Donkey Kong title screen</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello. I'm working on a Donkey Kong hack for a friend of mine. I already edited some sprites and tiles with yy-chr. Now I'd like to create a new title on the title screen. I know that one single tile is used to create "DONKEY KONG". I want to take that tile and rearrange it. In the PPU memory view of the hex editor of FCEUX I see the tile ID's but when I change them and save, it won't stay. So can someone help me with this please?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
